 ${python3:Depends},
Description: client library for the Hugging Face Hub (Avalan PPA transitive)
 huggingface-hub is the client library for downloading and publishing
 models, datasets, and Spaces on the Hugging Face Hub. This package
 is built for the Avalan PPA because diffusers (Avalan's vendor)
 requires `>= 0.34.0`, while Noble's archive ships 0.20.3. Pinned at
 0.34.0 -- the minimum that satisfies diffusers and the last release
 line before huggingface-hub started requiring the much larger Rust
 dependency surface in its 1.x series.
 .
 The optional `hf-xet` accelerator (Rust-based Xet protocol client)
 is intentionally not declared as a Depends here: it lives behind
 try/except ImportError guards in every Xet code path inside
 huggingface_hub, so the HTTP-only paths Avalan actually uses keep
 working without it. Callers who want Xet acceleration can install
 `hf_xet` separately into a venv.
